title: Exceptional Primary Education Completion
description: In 2021, Spain achieved a near-perfect primary education completion rate, with 99.97% of students persisting to grade 5 and 99.94% reaching the last grade of primary school.

title: Minimal Financial Strain from Healthcare Costs
description: As of 2019, only 0.01% of Spain's population was pushed further below the $3.65 poverty line due to out-of-pocket healthcare expenses, indicating minimal financial strain from healthcare costs.
